  "text": "I have a question here from Jim. It states, I believe that one of my primary pre-incarnative choices was to open my Green Green Energy Center for healing purposes. As I see my compassion developing, is it more appropriate to balance this compassion with wisdom? And my healing exercises are to allow the compassion to develop as much as possible without being balanced. This query borders upon that type of question to which answers are unavailable due to the free will prohibitions upon information from the teach learners to the student of the balancing process, we may suggest that the most stringent honesty be applied as compassion is perceived. Thus these student may discover many other components to what may seem to be all embracing love. Each of these components may be balanced and accepted as part of the self and as transitional material as the entity's seat of a learn teaching moves ever fairly into the green ray when it is perceived that universal love has been achieved the next balancing may or may not be a wisdom if the adept is a balancing manifestations. If the balancing is of mind or spirit, there are many subtleties to which the adept may give careful consideration. Shall we say, but faces of the same coin, if you will.",
